"title": "5157: head",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5157",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The position of the head often expresses an attitude or emotion. Figuratively head may mean “chief”, “first” or “top”.</p>\n<h2>The head as part of the body</h2>\n<h3>Heads of people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:11\">GEN 28:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:18\">GEN 28:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:14\">GEN 48:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:17\">GEN 48:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:26\">JDG 5:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:6\">SNG 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:5\">JON 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Heads of animals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:9\">EXO 12:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:4\">LEV 1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:25\">2KI 6:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:1\">EXO 22:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:23\">1KI 4:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:11\">2CH 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:9\">2CH 35:9</a></p>\n<h3>Heads of idols</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:4\">1SA 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:13\">1SA 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:16\">1SA 19:16</a></p>\n<h2>The head as the uppermost part of the body</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:12\">LEV 13:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:25\">2SA 14:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:7\">JOB 2:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:6\">ISA 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:13\">HAB 3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:9\">JHN 13:9</a></p>\n<h3>A measure of height</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:2\">1SA 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:23\">1SA 10:23</a></p>\n<h3>A crown worn on the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:10\">2SA 1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:17\">EST 2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:3\">PSA 21:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:18\">JER 13:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:16\">LAM 5:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:11\">ZEC 6:11</a></p>\n<h3>A turban worn on the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:9\">LEV 8:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:15\">EZK 23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:5\">ZEC 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Death and decapitation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:19\">GEN 40:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:46\">1SA 17:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:51\">1SA 17:51</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:7\">2SA 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:9\">2SA 16:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:8-Matt14:11\">MAT 14:8–14:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:24-Mark6:28\">MRK 6:24–6:28</a></p>\n<h2>Head used figuratively in various expressions</h2>\n<h3>``Be it on one's own head'': personal responsibility that is inescapable</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:9\">LEV 20:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:11-Lev20:13\">LEV 20:11–20:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:27\">LEV 20:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:19\">JOS 2:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:39\">1SA 25:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:16\">2SA 1:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:33\">1KI 2:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:10\">EZK 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:4-Ezek33:5\">EZK 33:4–33:5</a></p>\n<h3>``To come back on one's own head'': a wrongdoer suffering the very wrong he or she has committed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:32\">1KI 8:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:23\">2CH 6:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:4\">NEH 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:25\">EST 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:16\">PSA 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps140:9\">PSA 140:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:4\">JOL 3:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:7\">JOL 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15\">OBA 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>``To heap burning coals on his head'': generosity towards an enemy in the hope of causing a change of heart</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:22\">PRO 25:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:20\">ROM 12:20</a></p>\n<h3>``Not a hair on one's head will be lost'': absolute safety</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:45\">1SA 14:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:52\">1KI 1:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:27\">DAN 3:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:7\">LUK 12:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:34\">ACT 27:34</a></p>\n<h3>``To keep one's head'': staying calm</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:5\">2TI 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>``Making it up out of one's head'': imagining something</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh6:8\">NEH 6:8</a></p>\n<h3>``Blessing resting on your head''</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:26\">GEN 49:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:16\">DEU 33:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:6\">PRO 10:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals concerning the head</h2>\n<p>Cleansing after infectious skin diseases:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:9\">LEV 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:18\">LEV 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:29\">LEV 14:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:9\">NUM 6:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:5\">JDG 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:17\">JDG 16:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:11</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:12\">DEU 21:12</a></p>\n<h3>The anointing of the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:7\">EXO 29:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:7\">MAT 26:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a></p>\n<h2>Covering or uncovering the head in Christian worship</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:4-1Cor11:7\">1CO 11:4–11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:10\">1CO 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:13-1Cor11:15\">1CO 11:13–11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Expressions of grief involving the head</h2>\n<h3>Bowing the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:14\">PSA 35:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:10\">LAM 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Shaving the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1\">DEU 14:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa15:2\">ISA 15:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer47:5\">JER 47:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:37\">JER 48:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:18\">EZK 7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:30-Ezek27:31\">EZK 27:30–27:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:20\">EZK 44:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:10\">AMO 8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:16\">MIC 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Putting dust on the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">JOS 7:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:12\">1SA 4:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:2\">2SA 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:32\">2SA 15:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:1\">NEH 9:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:12\">JOB 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Covering the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:30\">2SA 15:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:12\">EST 6:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:3-Jer14:4\">JER 14:3–14:4</a></p>\n<h2>Various attitudes expressed with the head</h2>\n<h3>Lifting up the head in joy and expectation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:3\">PSA 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:6\">PSA 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:7\">PSA 110:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a></p>\n<h3>Bowing the head in humility</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:5\">ISA 58:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13\">LUK 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Hanging the head in shame and dejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:28\">JDG 8:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:15\">JOB 10:15</a></p>\n<h3>Shaking the head in scorn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:21\">2KI 19:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:22\">ISA 37:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:4\">JOB 16:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:25\">PSA 109:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:16\">JER 18:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:27\">JER 48:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:15\">LAM 2:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39\">MAT 27:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29\">MRK 15:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:7\">PSA 22:7</a></p>\n<h3>Rearing the head in rebellion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:2\">PSA 83:2</a></p>\n<h2>Head meaning <code>chief'' or</code>first''</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:10\">EPH 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22\">EPH 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:10\">COL 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:19\">COL 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>The head of a family, tribe or kingdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:14\">EXO 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:25\">EXO 6:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:4\">NUM 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:3\">NUM 17:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:8-Judg11:9\">JDG 11:8–11:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:8-Isa7:9\">ISA 7:8–7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:14-Isa9:15\">ISA 9:14–9:15</a></p>\n<h3>Man as the head</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3\">1CO 11:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:23\">EPH 5:23</a></p>\n<h2>Head meaning ``top''</h2>\n<h3>Head of a street</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:21\">PRO 1:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:20\">ISA 51:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:19\">LAM 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:1\">LAM 4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:25\">EZK 16:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:10\">NAM 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Head of a valley</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:1\">ISA 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:4\">ISA 28:4</a></p>\n<h3>Head of a table</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:22\">1SA 9:22</a></p>\n<h3>Head of a stalk of grain</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:14\">LEV 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:7\">HOS 8:7</a></p>\n<h3>Head of an axe</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:5\">DEU 19:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:5\">2KI 6:5</a></p>\n<h2>Head meaning ``front''</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:21\">2CH 20:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:11\">JOL 2:11</a></p>",
